## Problem to solve

Once the [DAST site profiles library](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/229514) and the [DAST site profile form](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/227244) are completed, the **Edit** links in the former should link to the latter.

Prior art: [GroupEntity](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/dc6fa0462cada162d6027b1a50fc0baed11d851a/app/serializers/group_entity.rb#L27-29)

## Implementation plan

~backend 

- [x] Extend the [`DastSiteProfiles` GraphQL query](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/231270) to expose the edit path which can be obtained with the `edit_project_dast_site_profile_path(project, dast_site_profile)` helper.

```patch
 query DastSiteProfiles($fullPath: ID!, $after: Int, $before: Int, $first: Int, $last: Int) {
   project(fullPath: $fullPath) {
     DastSiteProfiles(after: $after, before: $before, first: $first, last: $last) {
       pageInfo {
         hasNextPage
         hasPreviousPage
       }
       edges {
         cursor
         node {
           id,
           profileName,
           targetUrl,
+          editPath,
           validationStatus # stubbed until validation iteration is complete
         }
       }
     }
   }
 }
```

~frontend 

- [x] In the DAST site profiles list, retrieve the `editPath` and use it for as the href for **Edit** links.

